lctech f1c200s: set USB OTG to host mode for the CarPlay dongle

The board's single USB (OTG) is on the Type-C socket; a CarPlay /
Android-Auto dongle needs the SoC as USB host. The in-tree DTS defaults to
"peripheral" (gadget). Force host mode. NOTE: VBUS on this socket is tied to
the board Vin, so power the board from another source when hosting a dongle.

--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/suniv-f1c200s-lctech-pi.dts
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/suniv-f1c200s-lctech-pi.dts
@@ -67,7 +67,7 @@
  * otherwise), but peripheral is probably the intention.
  */
 &usb_otg {
-	dr_mode = "peripheral";
+	dr_mode = "host";
 	status = "okay";
 };
 
